Please be aware of 3 redacted elements in this bug report: [org-name], [project-name] and [repo-name].

I have configured a DevOps remote on my repository with extended integration.

As "Host Root Url" I have configured:

{{https://dev.azure.com/[org-name]/[project-name]}}

I expect Sourcetree to initiate a pull request on Azure DevOps in my browser after pushing by pressing CMD+Option+P in Sourcetree.

The result is a 404 page in my web browser with a URL formatted like:

{{https://dev.azure.com/[org-name]/[project-name]/[project-name]/_apis/git/repositories/[repo-name]/pullrequests?sourceRef=master?api-version=4.1}}

 

Ok fine, I see my project name in that url twice so I change the "Host Root Url" to:

{{https://dev.azure.com/[org-name]}}

Result is a bunch of json in my browser on the URL:

{{https://dev.azure.com/[org-name]/[project-name]/_apis/git/repositories/[repo-name]/pullrequests?sourceRef=master?api-version=4.1}}

 

I did notice that when I enter below URL in my browser I land on the page I am expecting to see when initiating a pull request from SourceTree:

{{https://dev.azure.com/[project-name]/[project-name]/_git/[repo-name]/pullrequestcreate?sourceRef=master}}
